## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="87fba-138">`Note to Inheritors` Se si esegue l'overload di questa funzione, e non può essere utilizzato per l'estensibilità.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="87fba-138">`Note to Inheritors` If you overload this function, it cannot be used for extensibility.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="87fba-139">Al contrario, si può restituire un elemento creato dalla classe di base, in questo caso, `XmlDataDocument`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="87fba-139">Instead, you can return an element created by the base class, in this case, `XmlDataDocument`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="87fba-140">Vedere l'esempio seguente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="87fba-140">See the following example.</span></span>  
  
```  
class MyXmlDataDocument : XmlDataDocument {  
 public override XmlElement CreateElement(string prefix, string localName, string nsURI) {  
   //Ensure we are returning the base class implementation of element.  
   XmlElement e = base.CreateElement(prefix, localName, nsURI);  
   //Add additional code here.  
   return e;    //Return the element created by XmlDataDocument.  
 }      
}  
```
